{"key":"processedPost-6503507","value":{"id":6503507,"first":6502211,"last":6505102,"when":1169962709,"utime":"01/28/07 07:38 AM","content":"Buds make an 'ok' substrate, but if it's trash for smoking, you have nothing to lose.  Molds grow well on hemp too as anybody who's left a bag of weed sitting damp for very long already knows.  If mold fungi will grow on it, mushroom fungi is likely to grow as well.  That's what led me to colonize the WW.  The burrito above is hemp canvas rolled up.  The cave bee is the same hemp canvas material sewn into the shape.  The 'head' was left dry and not inoculated to retain the color.<br /><br />Oh yea, I forgot one.  Ball of twine starts with a 'b'.<br />RR<br /><br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/05-13/208956206-hemp_log_002b.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/05-13/208956206-thumb_hemp_log_002b.jpg\"></a>","title":"Re: buds as substrate?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}